President Donald J. Trump spoke with Prime Minister Theresa May of the United Kingdom and they agreed that the Syrian regime and its Russian and Iranian sponsors must implement UN Security Council Resolution 2401 for an immediate ceasefire across Syria. They condemned the bombing in East Ghouta and stated that the US and UK will hold Russia accountable for compelling the Assad regime to stop attacks on civilian areas and provide humanitarian relief in East Ghouta. They also criticized Russian President Vladimir Putin's recent statements on nuclear weapons development. Other topics discussed included President Trump's efforts on fair and reciprocal trade and Prime Minister May's work on Brexit negotiations.